♻️ Real-Time Waste Classification & Carbon Impact Monitoring

🚀 An AI-powered real-time waste classification system built for Hack For Green Bharat.

This project leverages Deep Learning + FastAPI + Pathway Streaming to automatically classify waste images and monitor waste trends in real time, enabling smarter and more sustainable waste management.

🌐 Live Demo
🔗 Backend API:
https://hack-for-green-bharat-wx1i.onrender.com
🔗 API Documentation (Swagger UI):
https://hack-for-green-bharat-wx1i.onrender.com/docs
🎯 Problem Statement

Improper waste segregation leads to:

🚫 Increased landfill overflow
🌫️ Higher carbon emissions
🌍 Environmental pollution
♻️ Poor recycling efficiency

👉 There is a need for an intelligent system that can:

Automatically classify waste
Track waste generation trends
Estimate carbon impact
Support sustainability decisions
🧠 Solution Overview

Green AI is a real-time intelligent waste monitoring system that:

📸 Accepts waste image uploads
🤖 Classifies waste using a deep learning model (ResNet18)
📊 Logs predictions into a streaming pipeline
⚡ Uses Pathway for real-time aggregation
📈 Displays live waste distribution statistics
🌱 (Optional) Estimates carbon impact
🏗️ System Architecture
Frontend (Vercel)
        ↓
FastAPI Backend (Render)
        ↓
AI Model (PyTorch - ResNet18)
        ↓
Waste Log (CSV)
        ↓
Pathway Streaming Engine
        ↓
Live Dashboard Data
🛠️ Tech Stack
🤖 AI / Machine Learning
PyTorch
ResNet18 (Fine-tuned)
Custom Waste Dataset (6 Classes)
⚙️ Backend
